100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 6, 1926, the world witnessed significant developments as the League of Nations held discussions on disarmament, aiming to address rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the Senate continued to debate the contentious issue of Prohibition, with opinions sharply divided over its enforcement. Meanwhile, in the realm of science, news of advances in radio technology was stirring excitement, hinting at a future where communication would transform lives across the globe.
